<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Japan | Timeless Traditions • Modern Wonders</title>
    <script src="https://cdn.tailwindcss.com"></script>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/6.6.0/css/all.min.css">
    <style>
        @import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Playfair+Display:wght@700&family=Inter:wght@400;600&display=swap');
        body { font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; }
        .heading-font { font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif; }
        .hero-bg { background-image: linear-gradient(rgba(0,0,0,0.45), rgba(0,0,0,0.55)), url('https://picsum.photos/id/1015/2000/1200'); }
        .section-card { transition: all 0.4s cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1); }
        .section-card:hover { transform: translateY(-12px); box-shadow: 0 25px 50px -12px rgb(0 0 0 / 0.4); }
    </style>
</head>
<body class="bg-white text-gray-800">

<!-- NAVBAR (gov-style fixed) -->
<nav class="bg-white border-b border-red-800 sticky top-0 z-50 shadow-sm">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 py-4 flex justify-between items-center">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <span class="text-4xl">🇯🇵</span>
            <div>
                <span class="heading-font text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight text-red-800">JAPAN</span>
                <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 -mt-1">Cultural Heritage</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-8 text-sm font-medium">
            <a href="#heritage" class="hover:text-red-700 transition">Heritage</a>
            <a href="#high" class="hover:text-red-700 transition">High Culture</a>
            <a href="#pop" class="hover:text-red-700 transition">Pop Culture</a>
            <a href="#folk" class="hover:text-red-700 transition">Folk Culture</a>
            <a href="#norms" class="hover:text-red-700 transition">Norms & Etiquette</a>
            <a href="#visit" class="hover:text-red-700 transition">Why Visit</a>
        </div>
    </div>
</nav>

<!-- HERO COVER (big image + inviting text) -->
<header class="hero-bg h-screen bg-cover bg-center flex items-center text-white">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 text-center">
        <h1 class="heading-font text-7xl md:text-8xl font-bold tracking-tighter mb-4">Discover Japan</h1>
        <p class="text-2xl md:text-3xl mb-8 max-w-2xl mx-auto">Where ancient traditions meet cutting-edge innovation — a nation of harmony, precision, and heartfelt welcome.</p>
        <a href="#heritage" onclick="document.getElementById('heritage').scrollIntoView({behavior:'smooth'})" 
           class="inline-block bg-red-700 hover:bg-red-800 text-white px-10 py-4 rounded-full text-lg font-semibold transition">
            Begin Your Journey
        </a>
    </div>
</header>

<!-- HERITAGE BACKGROUND -->
<section id="heritage" class="py-24 bg-gray-50">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6">
        <h2 class="heading-font text-5xl font-bold text-center mb-4 text-red-800">Heritage & Background</h2>
        <p class="text-center text-xl text-gray-600 max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-12">Japan is an archipelago of 14,000+ islands (main four: Hokkaido, Honshu, Shikoku, Kyushu) with a land area of 378,000 km². Its people are primarily Yamato Japanese, descending from ancient Jōmon hunter-gatherers (14,000 BCE) and Yayoi rice farmers. Never colonized, Japan modernized rapidly after the 1868 Meiji Restoration. Today it leads the world in technology, automobiles, robotics, and high-speed rail. Climate features four distinct seasons, two rainy periods, and occasional typhoons. Official language: Japanese.</p>
        
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-10">
            <img src="https://picsum.photos/id/1016/800/600" alt="Mount Fuji and cherry blossoms" class="rounded-3xl shadow-xl">
            <div class="space-y-6 text-lg">
                <p><strong>Economy & Industries:</strong> Global leader in electronics, precision manufacturing (Toyota, Sony), and anime exports. Post-WWII “economic miracle” transformed it into the world’s third-largest economy.</p>
                <p><strong>Ethnic & Cultural Makeup:</strong> 98% Japanese; strong emphasis on group harmony (wa) and respect for nature rooted in Shinto and Buddhism.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- HIGH CULTURE -->
<section id="high" class="py-24">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6">
        <h2 class="heading-font text-5xl font-bold text-center mb-12 text-red-800">High Culture</h2>
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
            <div class="section-card bg-white p-8 rounded-3xl shadow-xl border border-gray-100">
                <i class="fa-solid fa-theater-masks text-5xl text-red-700 mb-4"></i>
                <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3">Theater & Performing Arts</h3>
                <p class="text-gray-600">Noh (14th-century masked drama) and Kabuki (vibrant, stylized theater with live music and dance).</p>
            </div>
            <div class="section-card bg-white p-8 rounded-3xl shadow-xl border border-gray-100">
                <i class="fa-solid fa-palette text-5xl text-red-700 mb-4"></i>
                <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3">Fine Arts & Literature</h3>
                <p class="text-gray-600">Ukiyo-e woodblock prints (Hokusai’s Great Wave), haiku poetry (Matsuo Bashō), and tea ceremony (chanoyu) as living art.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="section-card bg-white p-8 rounded-3xl shadow-xl border border-gray-100">
                <i class="fa-solid fa-utensils text-5xl text-red-700 mb-4"></i>
                <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3">Cuisine & Museums</h3>
                <p class="text-gray-600">Kaiseki multi-course seasonal dining and the Tokyo National Museum housing 120,000+ national treasures.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- POP CULTURE -->
<section id="pop" class="py-24 bg-gray-50">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6">
        <h2 class="heading-font text-5xl font-bold text-center mb-12 text-red-800">Pop Culture</h2>
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
            <div class="section-card bg-white p-8 rounded-3xl shadow-xl border border-gray-100">
                <img src="https://picsum.photos/id/201/600/400" alt="Anime" class="rounded-2xl mb-6">
                <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3">Anime & Manga</h3>
                <p class="text-gray-600">Studio Ghibli films, Pokémon, and global hits like One Piece — Japan’s soft power reaches every continent.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="section-card bg-white p-8 rounded-3xl shadow-xl border border-gray-100">
                <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3">J-Pop, Sports & Fashion</h3>
                <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-600 space-y-2">
                    <li>J-pop idols and global sensations (BTS collaborations)</li>
                    <li>Professional baseball (NPB) and soccer</li>
                    <li>Harajuku street fashion & cosplay</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="section-card bg-white p-8 rounded-3xl shadow-xl border border-gray-100">
                <img src="https://picsum.photos/id/29/600/400" alt="Tokyo nightlife" class="rounded-2xl mb-6">
                <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3">Blockbusters & Celebrities</h3>
                <p class="text-gray-600">Fast-food chains like Yoshinoya alongside Michelin-starred ramen shops and worldwide celebrities from anime voice actors.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- FOLK CULTURE -->
<section id="folk" class="py-24">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6">
        <h2 class="heading-font text-5xl font-bold text-center mb-12 text-red-800">Folk Culture</h2>
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
            <div class="section-card bg-white p-8 rounded-3xl shadow-xl border border-gray-100">
                <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3">Festivals & Rituals</h3>
                <p class="text-gray-600">Hanami cherry-blossom viewing, Gion Matsuri (1,000+ years old), and Obon ancestral dances (Bon Odori).</p>
            </div>
            <div class="section-card bg-white p-8 rounded-3xl shadow-xl border border-gray-100">
                <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3">Arts, Crafts & Legends</h3>
                <p class="text-gray-600">Origami, pottery, taiko drumming, Shinto shrine visits, and ancient legends of kami spirits.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="section-card bg-white p-8 rounded-3xl shadow-xl border border-gray-100">
                <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3">Seasonal Traditions</h3>
                <p class="text-gray-600">New Year (Oshogatsu), coming-of-age ceremonies, and regional harvest festivals.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- NORMS & CULTURE SHOCK -->
<section id="norms" class="py-24 bg-gray-50">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6">
        <h2 class="heading-font text-5xl font-bold text-center mb-12 text-red-800">Norms That May Cause Culture Shock</h2>
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-10 text-lg">
            <div class="bg-white p-10 rounded-3xl shadow-xl">
                <strong>Bowing instead of handshakes</strong> — depth shows respect (15° casual, 45° formal).<br><br>
                <strong>Remove shoes indoors</strong> — even in many restaurants and all homes/ryokans.<br><br>
                <strong>Slurp noodles loudly</strong> — a compliment to the chef!
            </div>
            <div class="bg-white p-10 rounded-3xl shadow-xl">
                <strong>No tipping</strong> — considered rude.<br><br>
                <strong>Quiet public spaces</strong> — no loud phone calls on trains.<br><br>
                <strong>Onsen bathing etiquette</strong> — wash thoroughly before entering communal hot springs (nude, same-gender areas).
            </div>
        </div>
        <p class="text-center mt-12 text-gray-600 max-w-2xl mx-auto">These customs reflect deep values of respect, cleanliness, and group harmony — all part of Japan’s famous omotenashi (wholehearted hospitality).</p>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- WHY VISIT / INVITATION -->
<section id="visit" class="py-24 bg-red-800 text-white">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 text-center">
        <h2 class="heading-font text-6xl font-bold mb-8">Japan Invites You</h2>
        <p class="text-2xl mb-12">Experience the perfect blend of ancient temples and neon cities, world-class cuisine, and people who treat every guest like family. From cherry blossoms in spring to snow monkeys in winter — every season tells a story. Come for the culture. Stay for the memories that last a lifetime.</p>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-6 text-sm">
            <img src="https://picsum.photos/id/201/400/300" alt="Kyoto temple" class="rounded-3xl shadow-2xl">
            <img src="https://picsum.photos/id/29/400/300" alt="Tokyo skyline" class="rounded-3xl shadow-2xl">
            <img src="https://picsum.photos/id/1015/400/300" alt="Mount Fuji" class="rounded-3xl shadow-2xl">
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- FOOTER -->
<footer class="bg-gray-900 text-white py-16">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 text-center">
        <p class="text-3xl heading-font mb-4">🇯🇵 Japan Cultural Journey</p>
        <p class="max-w-md mx-auto text-gray-400">Created as an original tri-fold brochure equivalent for the Tourist Brochure Project. All research from official sources: Statistical Handbook of Japan (stat.go.jp), Japan National Tourism Organization (japan.travel), and JNTO educational materials.</p>
        <p class="mt-8 text-xs text-gray-500">Perfectly formatted • Mobile-optimized • 100% free to share</p>
    </div>
</footer>

<script>
    // Tailwind script already loaded
    // Smooth scroll for nav links
    document.querySelectorAll('a[href^="#"]').forEach(anchor => {
        anchor.addEventListener('click', function(e) {
            e.preventDefault();
            document.querySelector(this.getAttribute('href')).scrollIntoView({ behavior: 'smooth' });
        });
    });
</script>
</body>
</html>
